payload/webos25/  --  webOS-25 (C5-class) decoder-inject payload
=================================================================

Profile: webos25-armel-gst124   (VERIFIED mechanism -- see ../../README.md)

Drop the two cross-built ARM soft-float (armel, EABI5) binaries HERE before
packaging the .ipk:

    payload/webos25/libgstdtsdec.so     patched dtsdec (gst-plugins-bad 1.22,
                                        sink caps widened to also accept
                                        audio/x-unknown, codec-id=A_DTS)
    payload/webos25/libdca.so.0         bundled DTS decode library (armel)

Where they come from
--------------------
Build them with the reproducible Docker cross-build in the repo:

    cd ../../../webos25
    ./build.sh                 # -> webos25/out/libgstdtsdec.so
                               #    webos25/out/libdca.so.0
    cp out/libgstdtsdec.so out/libdca.so.0 \
       ../dts-enabler-universal/payload/webos25/

At enable time the JS service copies these to:
    /var/lib/webosbrew/dts25/libgstdtsdec.so
    /var/lib/webosbrew/dts25/libs/libdca.so.0
(libgstdtsdec.so has RPATH baked to /var/lib/webosbrew/dts25/libs), then
regenerates the media GStreamer registry including dtsdec and bind-mounts it
over /mnt/flash/data/gst_1_0_registry.arm.bin. No LG library is overridden.

ABI constraints (must hold or the plugin will not load on the C5)
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  - 32-bit ARM, EABI5 soft-float  (loader ld-linux.so.3, e_flags 0x05000200)
  - max referenced GLIBC symbol <= 2.4  (TV has glibc 2.35)
  - GStreamer 1.22 plugin ABI (loads in the TV's 1.24 -- verified on-device)

These .so files are NOT committed (see ../../.gitignore). They are LGPL-2.1+;
ship the corresponding source offer with any distributed .ipk.
